{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892150945,"sessionID":"ses_2849470f8ffer9iOaI7vg9Ur0g","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6bb5d0001K1YEiAUbLNmxvJ","messageID":"msg_d7b6ba216001z1Hq6sN0bfm47o","sessionID":"ses_2849470f8ffer9iOaI7vg9Ur0g","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_547996e3b0a34f27bd7de96f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: <!-- TODO: Describe the purpose -->\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/\n13: ├── router/\n14: │   ├── *.go\n15: │   └── *_test.go         # TODO — new test files\n16: ├── store/\n17: │   ├── *.go\n18: │   └── *_test.go         # TODO — new test files\n19: └── picod/\n20:     ├── *.go\n21:     └── *_test.go         # TODO — new test files\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n25: \n26: - **Table-driven tests**: Go idiom for test data organization\n27: - **No production code changes**: Only `*_test.go` additions\n28: - **Interface-based mocking**: Abstract external dependencies behind interfaces\n29: - **Black-box + white-box**: Mix of `package_test` and `package_internal_test` as needed\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. Test Strategy by Sub-Package\n34: \n35: ### 2.1 router/\n36: \n37: | Test Category | Approach |\n38: |---------------|----------|\n39: | TODO | TODO |\n40: \n41: ### 2.2 store/\n42: \n43: | Test Category | Approach |\n44: |---------------|----------|\n45: | TODO | TODO |\n46: \n47: ### 2.3 picod/\n48: \n49: | Test Category | Approach |\n50: |---------------|----------|\n51: | TODO | TODO |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. Testing Patterns\n56: \n57: ### 3.1 Table-Driven Test Template\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: func TestFoo(t *testing.T) {\n61:     tests := []struct {\n62:         name       string\n63:         input      InputType\n64:         want       OutputType\n65:         wantErr    bool\n66:     }{\n67:         // TODO: add test cases\n68:     }\n69: \n70:     for _, tt := range tests {\n71:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n72:             // Arrange, Act, Assert\n73:         })\n74:     }\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 4. Coverage Targets\n81: \n82: | Sub-Package | Target Coverage | Rationale |\n83: |-------------|-----------------|-----------|\n84: | router/ | TODO | TODO |\n85: | store/ | TODO | TODO |\n86: | picod/ | TODO | TODO |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n91: \n92: <!-- TODO: Add implementation-specific notes -->\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\n<!-- TODO: Describe the purpose -->\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\npkg/\n├── router/\n│   ├── *.go\n│   └── *_test.go         # TODO — new test files\n├── store/\n│   ├── *.go\n│   └── *_test.go         # TODO — new test files\n└── picod/\n    ├── *.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/design.md","time":{"start":1775892150936,"end":1775892150943}}}}
