{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892154453,"sessionID":"ses_2849470f8ffer9iOaI7vg9Ur0g","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6bc20a001wKq1iyc5RRfgoe","messageID":"msg_d7b6ba216001z1Hq6sN0bfm47o","sessionID":"ses_2849470f8ffer9iOaI7vg9Ur0g","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dc2532d32199402d9c941c7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n4: **Base specs:** `pkg/router/`, `pkg/store/`, `pkg/picod/` source code\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: router/backend.go — Backend & HealthChecker\n10: \n11: - [ ] `TestBackend_String` — `String()` returns formatted `\"Backend{URL: ..., Healthy: ...}\"`\n12: - [ ] `TestNewBackendHealthChecker_Defaults` — constructor sets interval, fail/success thresholds, default checker\n13: - [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Success` — mock checker returns true → `ConsecutiveSuccess` increments, `Healthy` becomes true after threshold\n14: - [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Failure` — mock checker returns false → `ConsecutiveFail` increments, `Healthy` becomes false after threshold\n15: - [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_ResetOnSuccess` — after failures, success resets `ConsecutiveFail` to 0\n16: - [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_ResetOnFailure` — after successes, failure resets `ConsecutiveSuccess` to 0\n17: - [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Concurrent` — concurrent `Check` calls are thread-safe (no race)\n18: - [ ] `TestDefaultHealthChecker` — verify `defaultHealthChecker` constructs `/health` path and checks 2xx status (use httptest server)\n19: \n20: ## T-2: router/errors.go — Custom Error Types\n21: \n22: - [ ] `TestSessionNotFoundError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"session \\\"<id>\\\" not found\"`\n23: - [ ] `TestNewSessionNotFoundError` — constructor sets `SessionID` field\n24: - [ ] `TestSandboxTemplateNotFoundError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"sandbox template \\\"<ns>\\\"/<\\\"name\\\"> (kind=<kind>) not found\"`\n25: - [ ] `TestNewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError` — constructor sets Namespace, Name, Kind fields\n26: - [ ] `TestSessionTerminatedError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"session \\\"<id>\\\" has been terminated\"`\n27: - [ ] `TestNewSessionTerminatedError` — constructor sets `SessionID` field\n28: \n29: ## T-3: router/health.go — Health Endpoints\n30: \n31: - [ ] `TestHandleHealthLive` — returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n32: - [ ] `TestHandleHealthReady_WithSessionManager` — returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` when `sessionManager` is set\n33: - [ ] `TestHandleHealthReady_NoSessionManager` — returns 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}` when `sessionManager` is nil\n34: \n35: ## T-4: router/loadbalancer.go — Load Balancers\n36: \n37: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_EmptyBackends` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` for empty slice\n38: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_AllUnhealthy` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` when all backends unhealthy\n39: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_SingleHealthy` — selects the single healthy backend\n40: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_RoundRobin` — cycles through healthy backends in order across multiple calls\n41: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_SkipUnhealthy` — skips unhealthy backends during rotation\n42: - [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_Concurrent` — concurrent `Select` calls are thread-safe\n43: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_EmptyBackends` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` for empty slice\n44: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_AllUnhealthy` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` when all unhealthy\n45: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_MinConnections` — selects backend with fewest connections\n46: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_IncDec` — `Inc` increases connection count, `Dec` decreases\n47: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Inc_NewURL` — `Inc` initializes counter for unknown URL\n48: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Dec_UnknownURL` — `Dec` on unknown URL is a no-op (no panic)\n49: - [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_Concurrent` — concurrent `Select`/`Inc`/`Dec` calls are thread-safe\n50: \n51: ## T-5: router/router.go — Router Implementation\n52: \n53: - [ ] `TestNewRouter` — creates router with empty routes map and assigned load balancer\n54: - [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute` — adds route, subsequent `ServeHTTP` matches path\n55: - [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute_EmptyPattern` — empty pattern is a no-op (no error, no route added)\n56: - [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute_Duplicate` — adding same pattern twice is a no-op (no error)\n57: - [ ] `TestRouter_RemoveRoute` — removes route, subsequent `ServeHTTP` returns 404\n58: - [ ] `TestRouter_RemoveRoute_NonExistent` — removing non-existent route is a no-op\n59: - [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_NotFound` — unknown path returns 404\n60: - [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_UnhealthyBackend` — returns 503 with \"backend unhealthy\"\n61: - [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_LoadBalancerError` — returns 502 when load balancer returns error\n62: \n63: ## T-6: router/proxy.go — Proxy & Invoke Handlers\n64: \n65: - [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus` — extracts code and message from `apierrors.APIStatus`\n66: - [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus_ZeroCode` — defaults to 500 when status code is 0\n67: - [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus_InternalServerError` — overrides message to \"internal server error\" for 500\n68: - [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_GenericError` — returns 500 with \"internal server error\" for non-APIStatus errors\n69: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_EntryPointMatch` — selects entry point matching invocation path prefix\n70: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoMatchFallback` — falls back to first entry point when no prefix match\n71: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoEntryPoints` — returns 404 with \"no entry point found for sandbox\"\n72: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ProtocolPrefix` — prepends protocol to endpoint when missing `://`\n73: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_DefaultHTTP` — defaults to `http://` when no protocol specified\n74: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_InvalidURL` — returns 500 with \"invalid target URL\" for unparseable URL\n75: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ForwardedHeaders` — sets `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`\n76: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ExistingForwardedFor` — appends client IP to existing `X-Forwarded-For`\n77: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_JWTForSandbox` — generates and sets JWT `Authorization` header for Sandbox kind\n78: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_JWTForSandboxClaim` — generates and sets JWT `Authorization` header for SandboxClaim kind\n79: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoJWTForAgentRuntime` — does not set JWT header for AgentRuntime kind\n80: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_SessionIDHeader` — sets `x-agentcube-session-id` in response via `ModifyResponse`\n81: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ErrorHandler_ConnectionRefused` — returns 502 with \"sandbox unreachable\"\n82: - [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ErrorHandler_Timeout` — returns 504 with \"sandbox timeout\"\n83: - [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_SessionNotFound` — returns 404 when `GetSandboxBySession` returns `SessionNotFoundError`\n84: - [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_TemplateNotFound` — returns 404 when `GetSandboxBySession` returns `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError`\n85: - [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_StoreError` — delegates to `handleGetSandboxError` for other store errors\n86: - [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_NoEntryPoints` — returns 404 when sandbox has no entry points\n87: - [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_UpdateLastActivity` — calls `UpdateSessionLastActivity` before and after forwarding\n88: - [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke` — calls `handleInvoke` with `AgentRuntimeKind`\n89: - [ ] `TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke` — calls `handleInvoke` with `CodeInterpreterKind`\n90: \n91: ## T-7: router/session_manager.go — Session Manager\n92: \n93: - [ ] `TestNewSessionManager_MissingEnvVar` — returns error when `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n94: - [ ] `TestNewSessionManager_Success` — creates manager with store client, workload URL, and HTTP client\n95: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_WithSessionID` — calls `storeClient.GetSandbox` and returns result\n96: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_NotFound` — returns `SessionNotFoundError` when store returns `ErrNotFound`\n97: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_NoSessionID` — calls `createSandbox` then `CreateSession` when sessionID is empty\n98: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSession` — calls `storeClient.StoreSandbox` with sessionID and info\n99: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_UpdateSession` — calls `storeClient.UpdateSandbox`\n100: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_DeleteSession` — calls `storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n101: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_UpdateLastActivity` — calls `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()`\n102: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_ListSessions` — calls and returns `storeClient.ListSandboxes`\n103: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_AgentRuntime` — POSTs to `/v1/agent-runtime` for AgentRuntime kind\n104: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_CodeInterpreter` — POSTs to `/v1/code-interpreter` for CodeInterpreter kind\n105: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_DefaultKind` — defaults to `/v1/agent-runtime` for unknown kind\n106: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_NonOKResponse` — returns `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` on non-200 response\n107: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_EmptySessionID` — returns error when response has empty session ID\n108: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_DecodeError` — returns error on malformed JSON response\n109: - [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_Success` — returns populated `SandboxInfo` with entry points on success\n110: \n111: ## T-8: store/store.go — Store Interface & Singleton\n112: \n113: - [ ] `TestStorage_InterfaceCompliance` — `var _ store.Store = (*redisStore)(nil)` and `(*valkeyStore)(nil)` compile (interface compliance assertion)\n114: - [ ] `TestErrNotFound` — `ErrNotFound` error message is \"sandbox not found\"\n115: \n116: ## T-9: picod/types.go — Constants & Types\n117: \n118: - [ ] `TestConstants_Values` — `TimeoutExitCode == 124`, `MaxBodySize == 32<<20`, `PublicKeyEnvVar == \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `maxFileMode == 0777`\n119: - [ ] `TestExecuteRequest_RequiredBinding` — JSON binding validates `command` field is required\n120: - [ ] `TestUploadFileRequest_RequiredBinding` — JSON binding validates `path` and `content` fields are required\n121: \n122: ## T-10: picod/files.go — File Handlers (HTTP layer)\n123: \n124: - [ ] `TestSanitizePath_UninitializedWorkspace` — returns error when `workspaceDir` is empty\n125: - [ ] `TestSanitizePath_NormalPath` — returns clean path within workspace\n126: - [ ] `TestSanitizePath_PathTraversal` — rejects `../` traversal attempts\n127: - [ ] `TestSanitizePath_AbsolutePath` — strips leading separator, resolves within workspace\n128: - [ ] `TestSanitizePath_SymlinkEscape` — rejects symlinks pointing outside workspace\n129: - [ ] `TestUploadFileHandler_Multipart` — routes to `handleMultipartUpload` for `multipart/form-data` content type\n130: - [ ] `TestUploadFileHandler_JSON` — routes to `handleJSONBase64Upload` for JSON content type\n131: - [ ] `TestHandleMultipartUpload_MissingPath` — returns 400 when `path` form field is missing\n132: - [ ] `TestHandleMultipartUpload_MissingFile` — returns 400 when `file` form field is missing\n133: - [ ] `TestHandleMultipartUpload_Success` — writes file, returns 200 with FileInfo\n134: - [ ] `TestHandleMultipartUpload_PathTraversal` — returns 400 for traversal attempt in path\n135: - [ ] `TestHandleJSONBase64Upload_InvalidBase64` — returns 400 for invalid base64 content\n136: - [ ] `TestHandleJSONBase64Upload_Success` — decodes base64, writes file, returns 200 with FileInfo\n137: - [ ] `TestHandleJSONBase64Upload_CustomMode` — respects custom file mode from request\n138: - [ ] `TestListFilesHandler_MissingPath` — returns 400 when `path` query is missing\n139: - [ ] `TestListFilesHandler_Directory` — returns 200 with file list for valid directory\n140: - [ ] `TestListFilesHandler_NotFound` — returns 404 for non-existent directory\n141: - [ ] `TestListFilesHandler_NotDirectory` — returns error when path is not a directory\n142: - [ ] `TestDownloadFileHandler_Success` — returns file with correct Content-Type and headers\n143: - [ ] `TestDownloadFileHandler_NotFound` — returns 404 for non-existent file\n144: - [ ] `TestDownloadFileHandler_IsDirectory` — returns 400 when path is a directory\n145: - [ ] `TestDownloadFileHandler_DefaultContentType` — uses `application/octet-stream` for unknown extensions\n146: - [ ] `TestParseFileMode_Empty` — returns `0644` for empty string\n147: - [ ] `TestParseFileMode_Valid` — parses octal string correctly (e.g., `\"0755\"` → `0755`)\n148: - [ ] `TestParseFileMode_Invalid` — returns `0644` for non-octal string\n149: - [ ] `TestParseFileMode_OutOfRange` — returns `0644` when mode exceeds `maxFileMode`\n150: \n151: ## T-11: picod/files/chmod.go — Chmod\n152: \n153: - [ ] `TestFileManager_Chmod_Success` — changes file mode, returns response with formatted mode\n154: - [ ] `TestFileManager_Chmod_InvalidMode` — returns `ErrInvalidMode` for non-octal mode string\n155: - [ ] `TestFileManager_Chmod_ModeOutOfRange` — returns `ErrModeOutOfRange` for mode > 0777\n156: - [ ] `TestFileManager_Chmod_FileNotFound` — returns `ErrFileNotFound` for non-existent file\n157: - [ ] `TestFileManager_Chmod_PathTraversal` — returns `ErrPathTraversal` for `../` path\n158: \n159: ## T-12: picod/files/delete.go — Delete\n160: \n161: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_SinglePath` — deletes single file, returns in `Deleted` list\n162: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_SinglePath_Failure` — failure adds entry to `Failed` list\n163: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_SinglePath_Traversal` — traversal failure adds to `Failed` list\n164: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_BatchPaths` — deletes multiple files, populates `Deleted` and `Failed`\n165: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_BatchExceedsMax` — returns `ErrBatchSizeExceeded` when paths > `maxBatchSize`\n166: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DeleteFile_EmptyRequest` — returns empty response when no path or paths provided\n167: \n168: ## T-13: picod/files/download.go — Download & Range\n169: \n170: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_Success` — reads entire file, returns content with correct content type\n171: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_NotFound` — returns `ErrFileNotFound`\n172: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_IsDirectory` — returns `ErrIsDirectory`\n173: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_WithRange` — returns partial content (206) with `Content-Range` header\n174: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_RangeNotSatisfiable` — returns `ErrRangeNotSatisfiable` when start >= totalSize\n175: - [ ] `TestFileManager_DownloadFile_RangeClamped` — clamps end to totalSize-1 when end exceeds file size\n176: - [ ] `TestParseRange_Valid` — parses `\"bytes=0-99\"` → start=0, end=99\n177: - [ ] `TestParseRange_OpenEnd` — parses `\"bytes=100-\"` → start=100, end=totalSize-1\n178: - [ ] `TestParseRange_InvalidFormat` — returns error for missing `\"bytes=\"` prefix\n179: - [ ] `TestParseRange_InvalidStart` — returns error for non-numeric start\n180: - [ ] `TestParseRange_InvalidEnd` — returns error for non-numeric end\n181: - [ ] `TestParseRange_StartGreaterThanEnd` — returns error when start > end\n182: \n183: ## T-14: picod/files/list.go — List Files\n184: \n185: - [ ] `TestFileManager_ListFiles_Success` — returns list of files with name, size, mode, isDir\n186: - [ ] `TestFileManager_ListFiles_NotFound` — returns `ErrFileNotFound` for non-existent directory\n187: - [ ] `TestFileManager_ListFiles_NotDirectory` — returns `ErrNotADirectory` for file path\n188: - [ ] `TestFileManager_ListFiles_EmptyDirectory` — returns empty files list\n189: - [ ] `TestFileManager_ListFiles_PathTraversal` — returns `ErrPathTraversal` for `../` path\n190: \n191: ## T-15: picod/files/mkdir.go — MkDir\n192: \n193: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_CreateNew` — creates directory, returns `Created: true`\n194: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_AlreadyExists` — returns `Created: false` when directory already exists\n195: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_PathIsFile` — returns `ErrPathAlreadyExists` when path is a file\n196: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_CustomMode` — creates directory with specified mode\n197: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_DefaultMode` — creates directory with mode 0755 when mode not specified\n198: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_NestedPath` — creates nested directories (MkdirAll behavior)\n199: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MkDir_PathTraversal` — returns `ErrPathTraversal` for `../` path\n200: \n201: ## T-16: picod/files/move.go — Move/Rename\n202: \n203: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MoveFile_Success` — renames file from source to destination\n204: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MoveFile_SourceNotFound` — returns `ErrFileNotFound` when source doesn't exist\n205: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MoveFile_DestDirNotFound` — returns error when destination parent directory doesn't exist\n206: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MoveFile_PathTraversal_Source` — returns `ErrPathTraversal` for traversal in source\n207: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MoveFile_PathTraversal_Dest` — returns `ErrPathTraversal` for traversal in destination\n208: \n209: ## T-17: picod/files/search.go — Search\n210: \n211: - [ ] `TestFileManager_SearchFiles_MatchFound` — finds files matching glob pattern\n212: - [ ] `TestFileManager_SearchFiles_NoMatch` — returns empty matches when no files match\n213: - [ ] `TestFileManager_SearchFiles_MaxResults` — truncate