0: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFile_CreateParentDirs` — creates parent directories automatically\n241: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFile_CustomMode` — respects custom file mode\n242: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFileChunked_SingleChunk` — writes file directly when chunkTotal <= 1\n243: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFileChunked_MultipleChunks` — writes chunk files to tempDir\n244: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFileChunked_LastChunkTriggersMerge` — calls `mergeChunks` on final chunk\n245: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFileChunked_InvalidBase64` — returns `ErrInvalidBase64`\n246: - [ ] `TestFileManager_UploadFileChunked_ChunkTooLarge` — returns `ErrChunkTooLarge` when data > maxChunkSize\n247: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MergeChunks` — merges chunk files in order into final file, cleans up chunks\n248: - [ ] `TestFileManager_MergeChunks_MissingChunk` — returns error when a chunk file is missing\n249: - [ ] `TestFileManager_CleanupChunks` — removes all chunk files for a given basename\n250: - [ ] `TestParseFileModeStr_Empty` — returns `0644` for empty string\n251: - [ ] `TestParseFileModeStr_Valid` — parses octal string correctly\n252: - [ ] `TestParseFileModeStr_Invalid` — returns `0644` for non-octal string\n253: - [ ] `TestParseFileModeStr_OutOfRange` — returns `0644` when mode exceeds MaxFileMode\n254: - [ ] `TestFormatFileMode` — formats file mode as 4-digit octal string (e.g., `\"0644\"`)\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Dependency Graph\n259: \n260: ```\n261: T-1  ──┐\n262: T-2  ──┤\n263: T-3  ──┤\n264: T-4  ──┤\n265: T-5  ──┤\n266: T-6  ──┤\n267: T-7  ──┤\n268: T-8  ──┤\n269: T-9  ──┤\n270: T-10 ──┤\n271: T-11 ──┤\n272: T-12 ──┤\n273: T-13 ──┤\n274: T-14 ──┤\n275: T-15 ──┤\n276: T-16 ──┤\n277: T-17 ──┤\n278: T-18 ──┤\n279: T-19 ──┤\n280: T-20 ──┘\n281:        │\n282:        ▼\n283:      T-21\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## Parallelizable Groups\n287: \n288: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n289: |-------|-------|---------------|\n290: | G1 | T-1 through T-20 | None (all independent) |\n291: | G2 | T-21 | All above |\n292: \n293: ## Coverage Targets Summary\n294: \n295: | Subpackage | Target | Current | Gap |\n296: |------------|--------|---------|-----|\n297: | `router/` | ≥80% | ~35% (4/12 files tested) | backend, errors, health, informer, loadbalancer, proxy, router, session_manager |\n298: | `store/` | ≥80% | ~70% (4/5 files tested) | store.go (interface + singleton) |\n299: | `picod/` | ≥80% | ~55% (6/8 files tested) | files.go, types.go |\n300: | `picod/files/` | ≥80% | ~22% (4/18 files tested) | chmod, delete, download, list, mkdir, move, search, stat, types, upload |\n301: | **Overall** | **≥80%** | **~45%** | **~35% gap** |\n302: \n303: ## T-21: Run full test suite and verify coverage\n304: \n305: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -v` — all tests pass\n306: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out` — generate coverage report\n307: - [ ] `go tool cover -func=coverage.out` — review per-function coverage, verify ≥80% per subpackage\n308: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -race` — no race conditions detected\n309: - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...` — no vet warnings\n\n(End of file - total 309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `pkg` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n**Base specs:** `pkg/router/`, `pkg/store/`, `pkg/picod/` source code\n**Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n\n---\n\n## T-1: router/backend.go — Backend & HealthChecker\n\n- [ ] `TestBackend_String` — `String()` returns formatted `\"Backend{URL: ..., Healthy: ...}\"`\n- [ ] `TestNewBackendHealthChecker_Defaults` — constructor sets interval, fail/success thresholds, default checker\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Success` — mock checker returns true → `ConsecutiveSuccess` increments, `Healthy` becomes true after threshold\n- [ ] `TestBackendHeal